%I A396320 #20 May 28 2026 19:46:58
%S A396320 1,1,3,14,165,14296,87602831
%N A396320 Number of inequivalent strict ternary closure operators on a set of n elements.
%C A396320 A closure operator cl on a set X is strict if the empty set is closed; it is n-ary if for all subsets S of X, cl(A) being a subset of S for all subsets A of X with cardinality no more than n implies that S is closed.
%C A396320 a(n) is also the number of non-isomorphic ternary convexities on a set of n elements (see Kubiś).
%H A396320 Wiesław Kubiś, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/PL00012529">Separation properties of convexity spaces</a>, Journal of Geometry 74 (2002), pp. 110-119.
%H A396320 Tian Vlasic, <a href="/A396320/a396320.py.txt">Python Program</a>
%H A396320 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Closure_operator">Closure operator</a>.
%F A396320 a(n) <= A108798(n).
%e A396320 The a(3)=14 inequivalent systems are ({} and {1,2,3} not shown):
%e A396320   {1,2}
%e A396320   {1}
%e A396320   {1},{2}
%e A396320   {1},{1,2}
%e A396320   {1,2},{2,3}
%e A396320   {1},{2},{1,2}
%e A396320   {1,2},{1,3}
%e A396320   {1},{2},{3}
%e A396320   {1},{1,2},{1,3}
%e A396320   {1},{1,2},{2,3}
%e A396320   {1},{2},{1,2},{1,3}
%e A396320   {1},{2},{3},{1,2},{1,3}
%e A396320   {1,2},{1,3},{2,3}
%e A396320   {1},{2},{3},{1,2},{1,3},{2,3}
%Y A396320 Cf. A395658, A364656, A334255, A358144, A358152, A356544.
%Y A396320 Cf. A108798.
